# üêû bug report

### Affected Package
The issue is caused by package @angular/zone.js.


### Is this a regression?
AFAICT, it has always been like this.


### Description
W3C event handlers are supposed to be called regardless if one of them throws an exception.
However when global callback handling is used (default), if any of the registered event handlers result in an unhandled exception, execution of all remaining handlers is aborted. This represents a significant and hard-to-detect breakage in event handling just from loading ZoneJS.

https://github.com/angular/angular/blob/51bb922a081a1059929cb549ffbc3cf1d1366e2a/packages/zone.js/lib/common/events.ts#L150-L155


## üî¨ Minimal Reproduction
When run w/o ZoneJS, clicking the button prints both `click 1` and `click 2`.
When run with ZoneJS loaded, only `click 1` is printed.

```javascript
(function() {
  const btn = document.body.appendChild(document.createElement('button'));
  btn.textContent = 'Click me';

  btn.addEventListener('click', () => {
    console.log('click 1');
    throw new Error();
  });

  btn.addEventListener('click', () => {
    console.log('click 2');
  });
})()
```

Hi,
I have just encountered a sudden issue:

**Error in src/styles.css
Error: ENOENT: No such file or directory., '/dev/null'**

This suddenly started to happen.
There was no issue and my angular project we working just fine the all of a sudden the issue occurred without any changes to the project on my account.

It's like the following was suddenly unavailable:

@import '~@angular/material/prebuilt-themes/purple-green.css';

It feels like someone has moved the prebuilt-themes to another path?

Same issue happens in all my previous angular projects that uses the "@import '~@angular/material/prebuilt-themes/" .
They have been fine for a year now we have an issue?

Please try it yourself...   Simply add the following standard code  into your styles.css :

@import '~@angular/material/prebuilt-themes/purple-green.css';

#### Feature Description

Allow to add more then 3 colors in themes (primary/accent/warn).

#### Use Case
```scss
// What's in use right now
$theme: mat-light-theme(
  (
    color: (
      primary: mat-palette($blue),
      accent: mat-palette($green),
      warn: mat-palette($red),
    ),
  )
);

// The feature request
$theme: mat-light-theme(
  (
    color: (
      primary: mat-palette($blue),
      accent: mat-palette($green),
      warn: mat-palette($red),
      custom: mat-palette($custom),
    ),
  )
);

```
